@P TECSL-AR-A-CORE-SIGMAPHI = sigma(n)*phi(n) = n*tau(n)  iff  n in {1, 6}  (verified to 10^10, Rust 330s) :: foundation [11*REPO_INVARIANT]
  => "Discovery 8A in README §Perfect Number Universal Expansion: 'σ·φ = n·τ has NO solution except n=1,6 among the first million integers.'"
  => "Equivalent to discovery 8B: σ/φ = n iff n in {1,6}; 'abundancy = divisor-to-totient ratio.'"
  => "Bridge ratio R(n) = σφ/(nτ): R(1)=1, R(6)=1, R(28)=4, asymptotic limit ∞ as p→∞ for Mersenne perfect P_p — Bridge identity is a unique zero-crossing at p=2 (n=6)."
  -> TECSL-AR-A-RIDENTITY, TECSL-AR-A-EGYPT-UNIQUE
  |> README.md L580-588 (Discovery 8A 🟩⭐⭐, all integers verified)
  |> math/README.md L62-66 (σ-system map, 206 characterizations, 152 hypotheses)
  |> docs/proofs/T0-01-sigma-perfect-6.md (foundation proof)
  |> docs/proofs/T1-26-phi-sigma-unique.md (squarefree analytic + non-squarefree numerical)
  |> n6-replication/results/report.md (Tier-1 test_only_solution_is_2_3_6 PASS)

