  => "R<n always (1-line proof); R-chain convergence; R<5: 24 values, d_box≈0.155 (Cantor fractal)."
  => "Im(R) ∩ Perfect Numbers = {6}: R(120)=6 unique pre-image among perfect numbers."
  => "Dual S(n) = στ/(nφ); S=1 ⟺ n=28; RS = (σ/n)² (abundancy²); R-S asymmetry 2051x."
  |> math/README.md L60-100 (σφ=nτ system map with 8 corollary characterizations)

@P TECSL-AR-A-SIGMAINV-2 = sigma_{-1}(6) = 1 + 1/2 + 1/3 + 1/6 = 2  iff  n is perfect (definitional restatement) :: foundation [11*REPO_INVARIANT]
